caption: The food at Saturday Morning Cafe was phenomenal! The seafood Omelette was my favorite. Packed with crabmeat and topped with some sauce and shrimp. The skillet was really delicious. Had to spice it up with some salt & pepper because the grits were bland, but after that the dish was a 5 ⭐️. The scrambled eggs were the best scrambled eggs I’ve had thus far. Chicken was well seasoned and fried crispy with the chicken & waffles and the blueberry pancakes were something delicious. Will definitely have to return to explore more of the menu options. Follow other reviews @ IG: eat_n_critique.

Cute little spot in the Baltimore Harbor, the wait was long to get in and to get our food so I suggest you get there early. The service and the food was good. They just ran out of certain food products too soon. The waiter Ashley was very polite and helpful. She held the whole downstairs by herself and did great.

Very poor communication! Yesterday though, I had great service and a very friendly waitress. Today I went back here, and I had a different server at the bar. I asked for a breakfast sandwich (craft sandwich). I even pointed at the menu. After waiting a long time, they gave me the wrong sandwich. I get that everyone makes mistakes. I wasn’t even upset about that. I was upset that they didn’t even apologize or take responsibility  for the error. The manager did suggest they could make the correct sandwich. But I was disgusted by the service and how the situation was handled. I told them politely I was going to leave and the manager didn’t even care. I found the friendly waitress that I had yesterday  and explained the situation. She apologized on their behalf, and I felt bad that she had to do that. I don’t understand how that white trash manager even became a manager. An incredibly disgusting person and a disgrace! I’m not returning and I hope that white trash manager gets fired!

We spilled coffee on the table due to the unstable table (waiter made minimal effort to fix the table), we let the server know and it took them 15 minutes to come out and clean so we just moved tables. How is this place still open? Given the name is Saturday morning cafe, it is currently a Saturday morning here as we sit here. The least they can do is have decent service on Saturday mornings, pretty sure that's not a lot to ask for.  Finally got the food and it's so frustrating because it was decent. If you come, make sure you eat a full meal before because by the time you get your food you will be starving again and a year older.

Quaint location and style. Overall, was not a great experience. Walking in, it was a bit crowded, and none of the staff made an effort to greet us. We almost left before being seated, because we thought the host[?] didn't realize we were even there waiting. Not long after being seated, we were ready to make our order, but our waitress came and left with our request for coffee and water before we could even tell her we were ready. She brought the coffee, but not our waters. We couldn't request the water again, because she didn't return to check on us. The coffee was burned foldgers that tasted like the uncleaned pot it was probably brewed in. I ordered the Seafood Benedict, which tasted good overall, but the eggs were definitely overcooked, with no runny yolks whatsoever. The spinach and tomato (one of the things that sets it apart from the Baltimore Benedict) were on the side surprisingly. What was confusing is that my husband's Baltimore Benedict had the same. The only thing that made the orders different was the single piece of shrimp on each egg on the Seafood Benedict, and that it lacked hollandaise. But then again, my husband's Baltimore Benedict lacked the hollodaise. They also were unable to fulfill the fruit cup side that was listed on the menu. The potatoes I ordered instead were well-seasoned, and had good texture. The crab was also well-seasoned, and probably the most enjoyable part of the dish. Unfortunately though, the food was cold. It took about 25 mins for our orders to come out. Throughout our entire visit, the staff were not personable at all.

Very please with the food. The shrimp and grits was really good, served with homemade biscuits on a skillet. The resturant space is small, so we ate outside. Staff was nice, very good food. At that point we politely asked for the check.  I thought it couldn't be more than 5.00 for an ice tea and a Pepsi.  It was actually 6.35. I tipped an additional 1.00 and left.  I can't judge the food as I didn't get any but wouldn't recommend based off of my experience.

I usually hesitate to leave bad reviews for local eateries, but this one had so many recent 5 star ratings that I wanted to put a warning out. We waited 1.5 hours for our food. I finished my first cup of coffee in the first 20min, but had to wait another hour till I could get a refill. The food wasn't bad, but my French toast only had mounds of whipped cream and no syrup was provided. Unfortunately it was quite dry, and the pearl like sprinkles on top made my mouth bleed slightly and caused my boyfriend to exclaim in pain. Not sure if our experience is an outlier, but as a Kansan who wasted one of my limited chances to try local food this was a total disappointment. I think the manager realized, because he took my receipt from my hand and guided us to the register, presumably to make sure we wouldn't ditch the check. They took 10% off of our $30 for 2 people tab, but as someone who would never dine and ditch it seems very derogatory. Should have paid for the first cup of coffee and gotten breakfast at the starbucks nearby.
